         <abstract>
            <p>A matrix triangularization interpretation is given for the recursive algorithms computing the Pade approximants along a certain path in the Pade table, which makes it possible to unify all known algorithms in this field [5], [6]. For the normal Pade table, all these results carry over to the matrix Pade problem in a straightforward way. Additional features, resulting from the noncommutativity are investigated. A generalization of the Trench-Zohar algorithm and related recursions are studied in greater detail.</p>
          </abstract>
